##Exercise 1: Use R to figure out how many elements in the vector below are greater than 2 . (You need to filter out the NAs first) rooms <- c(1, 2, 1, 3, 1, NA, 3, 1, 3, 2, 1, NA, 1, 8, 3, 1, 4, NA, 1, 3, 1, 2, 1, 7, 1, NA)

#create object
rooms <- c(1, 2, 1, 3, 1, NA, 3, 1, 3, 2, 1, NA, 1, 8, 3, 1, 4, NA, 1, 3, 1, 2, 1, 7, 1, NA)

#remove na's
rooms_clean <- na.omit(rooms)
rooms_clean
##  [1] 1 2 1 3 1 3 1 3 2 1 1 8 3 1 4 1 3 1 2 1 7 1
## attr(,"na.action")
## [1]  6 12 18 26
## attr(,"class")
## [1] "omit"
#count how many elements are greater than 2
sum(rooms_clean > 2)
## [1] 8

##Exercise 2: What is the result of running median() function on the above ‘rooms’ vector? (again, best remove the NAs)

#apply median function 
median(rooms_clean)
## [1] 1.5

The median() function on the “rooms” vector (or in my case rooms_clean, which has no NA’s) gives 1.5.
